<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="560" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species seems closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" box="[788,1256,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorohovi">
<emphasis box="[788,1022,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">Chinoperla gorohovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[1029,1256,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" pagination="62 - 74" refId="ref2190" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2010) Five new species of Chinoperla Zwick (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam and Thailand. Illiesia, 6 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="2010">Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by similar head and leg patterns and aedeagal spine of aedeagal sac. However, the new species can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorohovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">C. gorohovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter, spinulose median sclerite of tergum 9, a slender rhomboid sclerite on aedeagal tube, presence of a nipple-like ventral lobe, and much longer apical spine of aedeagal sac (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1101,1232,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,561,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[158,1429,561,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Chinoperla longispina sp. nov. (male) A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia before NaOH treatment, dorsal view. C. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. D. Cleared terminalia, oblique lateral view." pageId="5" pageNumber="558">Figs. 5A, C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1243,1313,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[217,1355,181,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[217,1370,181,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Chinoperla longispina sp. nov. (male) A. Aedeagus, dorsal view. B. Aedeagus, ventral view. C. Aedeagus, lateral view. D. Aedeagus, apical spina, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="558">6B–D</figureCitation>
, with 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[201,1419,181,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-31@2.[158,1430,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male). A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia before NaOH treatment, dorsal view. C. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. D. Cleared terminalia, oblique lateral view." pageId="5" pageNumber="558">Figs. 2B–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[232,301,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1494,1518]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,181,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[167,1421,181,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male)A.Aedeagus, dorsal view.B.Aedeagus, ventral view. C.Aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="5" pageNumber="558">3A, C</figureCitation>
, in present study, and figs. 
<quantity box="[606,677,511,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" unit="in" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[684,935,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" pagination="62 - 74" refId="ref2190" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2010) Five new species of Chinoperla Zwick (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam and Thailand. Illiesia, 6 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="2010">Sivec &amp; Stark (2010))</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
