<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">
The aedeagal armatures of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yan &amp; Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Yan &amp; Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[501,652,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[501,652,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">C. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[659,748,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[659,748,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is also similar to the Vietnamese 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" box="[1123,1433,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sila">
<emphasis box="[1123,1196,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">C. sila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[1203,1433,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" pagination="62 - 74" refId="ref2190" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2010) Five new species of Chinoperla Zwick (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam and Thailand. Illiesia, 6 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="2010">Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" box="[301,377,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sila">
<emphasis box="[301,377,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">C. sila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, basal portion of aedeagal tube has lateral hairs which is not found in the new species and median process of tergum 9 of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" box="[496,569,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sila">
<emphasis box="[496,569,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">C. sila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more circular than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[890,1040,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina">
<emphasis box="[890,1040,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="560">C. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1256,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,561,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[158,1429,561,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Chinoperla longispina sp. nov. (male) A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia before NaOH treatment, dorsal view. C. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. D. Cleared terminalia, oblique lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="560">Figs. 5C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1267,1334,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[217,1355,181,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[217,1370,181,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Chinoperla longispina sp. nov. (male) A. Aedeagus, dorsal view. B. Aedeagus, ventral view. C. Aedeagus, lateral view. D. Aedeagus, apical spina, dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="560">6A, C</figureCitation>
and figs. 
<quantity box="[151,250,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" metricValueMax="6.096" metricValueMin="5.588" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" unit="in" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[257,508,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="560" pagination="62 - 74" refId="ref2190" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2010) Five new species of Chinoperla Zwick (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam and Thailand. Illiesia, 6 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="2010">Sivec &amp; Stark (2010))</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
